cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.HC 

This paper discusses a storage approach for digital objects and their constituent datastreams, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The use of XML and OAI-PMH for accessing digital objects suggests that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category. The use of ARC files and OpenURL for accessing datastreams suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) are also relevant sub-categories. The paper also discusses the creation of indexes, which is relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
